[{"location":"api/#AssortiveMatingABM.accept-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API","title":"AssortiveMatingABM.accept","text":"accept(agent1, agent2)\n\nAgent 1 compares its value to the value of agent 2. Agent 1 accepts agent 2 with a probability  defined by a probit model.\n\nArguments\n\nagent1: agent 1 of a potential pair  \nagent2: agent 2 of a potential pair \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#AssortiveMatingABM.does_match-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"API","title":"AssortiveMatingABM.does_match","text":"does_match(agent1, agent2)\n\nReturns true if the agents match and returns false otherwise. \n\nArguments\n\nagent1: agent 1 of a potential pair  \nagent2: agent 2 of a potential pair \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#AssortiveMatingABM","page":"Home","title":"AssortiveMatingABM","text":"Documentation for AssortiveMatingABM.","category":"section"},{"location":"example/","page":"Example","title":"Example","text":"using Agents\nusing AssortiveMatingABM\nusing GLM\nusing Plots\n\nmodel = initialize(;\n    n_agents = 1000,\n    μ = 0,\n    σ = 1,\n    λ = 0.50\n)\n\nrun!(model, stop)\n\nmatch_values = stack(model.match_values, dims = 1)\nlm_fit = lm(@formula(y ~ x), (; x = match_values[:, 1], y = match_values[:, 2]))\nscatter(\n    match_values[:, 1],\n    match_values[:, 2],\n    xaxis = \"agent 1 value\",\n    yaxis = \"agent 2 value\",\n    leg = false,\n    grid = false,\n    markersize = 2.5,\n    alpha = 0.50,\n    lims = (-4, 4)\n)\nx = -4:0.01:4\nplot!(x, predict(lm_fit, (; x)), color = :black, linestyle = :dash)\nβs = coef(lm_fit)\ntitle!(\"f(x) = $(round(βs[1], digits=2)) + x$(round(βs[2], digits=2))\")","category":"section"}]
